Virtual servers (VPS) and cloud servers are both based on virtualized infrastructures. 

The difference is usually in the specific technology used and the features. 

VPSs are usually physical servers that house CPU, RAM, and memory. 

Cloud infrastructures typically consist of separate compute and storage nodes, i.e., individual "cloudified" components.

With IONOS, the VPS is based on the same technology platform as the Cloud, but with a set of features
